## Architecture decisions

The following architecture decisions are APPROVED and SHALL be reflected consistently across all implementation documents.

### 1. Remove Execution Context Contract

Execution Context Contract is no longer part of the architecture.

Remove all references to:

- Execution Context Contract
- Execution Context object

Wherever it appears.

---

### 2. Remove Role Result Contract

Role Result Contract is no longer part of the architecture.

Lifecycle roles SHALL update Artifact Metadata directly.

Reporting Framework SHALL consume Artifact Metadata.

Remove all references to:

- Role Result Contract
- Role Result object

---

### 3. Artifact Metadata becomes the canonical runtime contract

Artifact Metadata is the single runtime object used throughout execution.

Every lifecycle role SHALL:

- read Artifact Metadata
- update runtime fields
- never modify Manifest

Reporting Framework SHALL consume Artifact Metadata.

Checkpoint Manager SHALL persist Artifact Metadata execution state.

Notification Framework SHALL consume Artifact Metadata or generated reports.

---

### 4. Approved execution flow

Replace every outdated execution flow with:

Manifest
    ↓
Manifest Validation
    ↓
Environment Resolver
    ↓
Artifact Metadata Builder
    ↓
Artifact Metadata
    ↓
Lifecycle Roles
    ↓
Checkpoint Manager
    ↓
Reporting Framework
    ↓
Notification Framework

---

### 5. Manifest is immutable

The Manifest SHALL never be modified after validation.

Runtime state SHALL exist only inside Artifact Metadata.

---

### 6. Environment Resolver

Environment Resolver is responsible for:

- loading environment template
- resolving Jinja2 variables
- producing resolved environment configuration

It SHALL execute before Artifact Metadata Builder.

---

### 7. Artifact Metadata Builder

Consumes:

- Validated Manifest
- Resolved Environment Configuration

Produces:

- Artifact Metadata

One Artifact Metadata object SHALL be created for every artifact.

